ange more fully into a truly integrative understanding of world history. CONTRIBUTORS: Michael Adas, William Beinart, Edmund Burke III, Mark Cioc, Kenneth Pomeranz, Mahesh Rangarajan, John F. Richards, Lise Sedrez, Douglas R. Weiner  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnvironmental sciencesxHistory. 0aHuman ecologyxHistory. 0aNaturexEffect of human beings onxHistory. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  aafrican environment.  acalifornia world history library.  achinese environment.  acommercialism.  adevelopmentalism.  aecology.  aenergy regimes.  aenvironmental change.  aenvironmental history.  aenvironmentalism.  afossil fuel revolution.  aglobal environment history.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ahuman history.  aimperialism.  aindian environment.  aindustrialization.  alatin american environment.  amiddle eastern environment.  apolitics of knowledge.  apopulation growth.  aproperty rights.  arussian environment.  asoutheast asian environment.  aworld history.1 aAdas, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeinart, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Edmund, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Edmund, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCioc, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPomeranz, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPomeranz, Kenneth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRangarajan, Mahesh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichards, John F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSedrez, Lise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat